docs.summary:
This method allows us to change the product to a different product
from the catalog, as long as they are of the same Type.
In other words this is the upgrade / downgrade path of a product.
"Business Unlimited" -> "Business VIP" or the other way around.
If this product instance was assigned to a site, the change will
happen without impacting the site - it is not "un-assign" than "assign" flow,
the site will remain with all of the functionality of the new product and if
there are common functionalities they would not be affected.

docs.summary:
Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN
  • DELIVERY_TIMEOUT - The delivery of the product took too long

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN
  • DAY - day
  • WEEK - week
  • MONTH - month
  • YEAR - year

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN
  • ONE_TIME
  • RECURRING

Possible values are:
  • PENDING
  • ENABLED
  • CANCELED
  • FAILED

Possible values are:
  • ASC
  • DESC

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN - unknown interval unit
  • DAY - day
  • WEEK - week
  • MONTH - month
  • YEAR - year

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN
  • SBS
  • LICENSER
  • BASS
  • RESELLER

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN
  • AUTO_RENEW_ON - Subscription will be renewed automatically at the end of the current payment cycle
  • AUTO_RENEW_OFF - Subscription will not be renewed at the end of the current payment cycle
  • MANUAL_RECURRING - Subscription will require user to manually renew
  • CANCELLED - Subscription has been cancelled
  • TRANSFERRED - Subscription has been transferred to a different account

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN
  • USER_REQUESTED - initiated by the user
  • REPLACED_BY_ANOTHER_SUBSCRIPTION - Another subscription was assigned to the site this subscription was assigned to
